## Capability vs Regression evals — two different jobs
direction: right

capability: {
  label: "CAPABILITY EVALS"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#dbeafe"
  style.stroke: "#2563eb"
  q: {label: "Question they answer:\n'Can the system handle\nNEW or harder cases?'"; shape: text}
  ex: {label: "Examples:\n• Hard SWE-bench problems\n• Novel reasoning tasks\n• New tool integration\n• New language / domain"; shape: text}
  cadence: {label: "Run when:\n• New model release\n• Major feature added\n• Quarterly capability review"; shape: text}
  metric: {label: "Metric: pass@k or absolute score\n(want to see ceiling raised)"; shape: text; style.font-color: "#16a34a"}
}

regression: {
  label: "REGRESSION EVALS"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#fde68a"
  style.stroke: "#d97706"
  q: {label: "Question they answer:\n'Did the change BREAK\nanything that worked before?'"; shape: text}
  ex: {label: "Examples:\n• Curated 'previously-passing' cases\n• Production-typical traffic\n• Known edge cases\n• Important customer flows"; shape: text}
  cadence: {label: "Run when:\n• Every PR\n• Every deploy\n• Before every prompt edit"; shape: text}
  metric: {label: "Metric: pass^k or score-delta\n(want to see no regressions)"; shape: text; style.font-color: "#d97706"}
}

both: {
  label: "Mature teams run BOTH"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#bbf7d0"
  style.stroke: "#16a34a"
  style.bold: true
  body: {label: "Capability evals tell you when to invest.\nRegression evals tell you when to ship.\nWithout capability: ceiling unknown.\nWithout regression: shipping breaks things."; shape: text}
}

capability -> both
regression -> both
